================================================================================
Notes on label derivation
================================================================================

For each test directory in the data branch, presence of an `error` file
indicates that the input is invalid YAML. The test corpus tags some inputs
under `tags/1.3-err/` and `tags/1.3-mod/` — these are errors only under
hypothetical YAML 1.3 semantics and are valid under YAML 1.2. setup.sh
filters those test IDs out of tests.jsonl so the corpus reflects YAML 1.2
ground truth.
